  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Quantity surveyor",
  "description": "<p><strong>Role & Responsibilty</strong></p><ul><li>Responsible for quantity take-offs and Cost Control functions for project.</li><li>Subcontracts management.</li><li>Preparation of monthly progress claims for work completed.</li><li>Tracking of Subcontractors/ Suppliers obligations required as per agreement.</li><li>Administering variations to subcontractors and suppliers.</li><li>Preparation of progress certificates for subcontractors and suppliers.</li><li>Assist in the preparation of the monthly cost reporting and forecasting.</li><li>Identification and pricing of variations to the Contract.</li><li>Assist in preparation of monthly commercial report.</li><li>Maintaining registers of variations, extension of time claims.</li><li>Liaising effectively with site engineers and supervisors to ensure all relevant information in relation to variations. and extension of time claims is captured.</li><li>Any other duties as may be required by the Company.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirement</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma / Degree</li><li>Minimum 2 to 5 years experience as a quantity surveyor</li><li>Able to work 6 days work week.</li><li>Passionate about Project values of safety & care, being honesty & integrity, customer focus, working together and performance excellence.</li></ul>",
